README:
This dataset was obtained in three sessions over two days with a single subject (PM), a competitive memory champion who uses the method of loci.

The four task types were:
1) task-loci: Walking through the (empty) loci
2) task-encode: Given one two-digit number at a time, construct a memorable event at each locus
3) task-recall: Recall events and corresponding numbers from most recent encoding session
4) task-forget: Walk through loci, attempting to remove associated event from memory
